column4: Tesla's Elon Musk  SEC again ask for more time to reach deal over CEO's Twitter use
column5: Tesla Inc Chief Executive Elon Musk and the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission on Thursday sought a second delay and requested to provide the court another joint submission on or before April 30  indicating whether they have reached an agreement to settle a dispute over Musk's use of Twitter  both parties said in a court filing.
